headline: Darden (DRI): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Since May 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 106%. But one standout stock has nearly doubled the market - over the past five years, Darden has surged 205% to $203.31 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 20.5% in the last six months, beating the S&P by 21.5%.
